WEBVTT

00:00.050 --> 00:01.070
<i>Hi, I'm Chuck.</i>

00:01.070 --> 00:02.700
<i>Here are a few things that
you might need to know.</i>

00:02.700 --> 00:05.080
Is there any way that Intersect
images can be taken out?

00:05.080 --> 00:06.055
Can it be removed?

00:06.133 --> 00:07.135
<i>Only Orion would know.</i>

00:07.170 --> 00:08.250
- Orion.
- <i>Hello, Chuck.</i>

00:08.250 --> 00:10.080
<i>It's good to finally
see you face-to-face.</i>

00:10.080 --> 00:11.363
<i>Those cards
you're looking at</i>

00:11.465 --> 00:12.650
<i>are the schematics
for the new Intersect.</i>

00:12.650 --> 00:13.176
<i>Study them.</i>

00:13.263 --> 00:14.660
<i>If you can find
FULCRUM's Intersect,</i>

00:14.660 --> 00:16.580
<i>you could get your
old life back.</i>

00:16.580 --> 00:18.870
I promised Ellie that I'd find
dad to walk her down the aisle

00:18.870 --> 00:20.337
<i>but I've tried everything.
He's nowhere;</i>

00:20.404 --> 00:22.174
<i>it's like he's fallen of the
face of the Earth.</i>

00:23.660 --> 00:24.488
Dad.

00:26.000 --> 00:32.073
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:36.630 --> 00:37.795
I'm sort of
freaking out here.

00:38.310 --> 00:39.030
I know.

00:39.030 --> 00:41.640
But he's your father,
and he seemed happy to see you.

00:41.640 --> 00:42.294
You think?

00:42.720 --> 00:45.087
I thought it was just lack of
recognition followed by shock.

00:45.330 --> 00:46.634
- You take cream?
- Huh?

00:48.100 --> 00:49.430
Yeah. No.

00:49.430 --> 00:50.280
Whatever's fine.

00:50.280 --> 00:52.113
I can't even remember
if I take cream.

00:52.350 --> 00:53.790
- Just relax.
- How?

00:53.790 --> 00:56.610
I-I haven't... I haven't seen
my dad for, like, ten years,

00:56.610 --> 00:59.970
and now I'm sitting in his
living room/kitchenette

00:59.970 --> 01:01.340
while he's making us coffee.

01:01.340 --> 01:03.907
Plus, let's just say the
last time I saw him,

01:04.030 --> 01:04.934
he was kind of--

01:05.630 --> 01:08.835
<i>I mean, he tended to be a little...</i>
What's the word? Crazy.

01:12.150 --> 01:13.197
Here we go.

01:13.640 --> 01:14.307
Thanks.

01:19.970 --> 01:21.605
So good to see
that face again.

01:25.650 --> 01:26.793
Yeah, yours, too.

01:29.900 --> 01:32.909
So, uh,
you doing okay?

01:33.340 --> 01:34.634
Who cares about me?

01:34.840 --> 01:35.859
Tell me about you.

01:36.120 --> 01:38.810
Uh, well, you know, there's not,
there's not much to tell.

01:38.810 --> 01:40.056
Graduated from
high school.

01:40.425 --> 01:42.185
Went to Stanford.
Work at Buy More.

01:42.320 --> 01:44.467
Stanford.
Not bad.

01:45.260 --> 01:47.043
He always was a genius--
this one.

01:48.620 --> 01:49.710
No, not like you.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.904
You're right.
He was smarter.

01:53.760 --> 01:55.010
What about Ellie?
How is she?

01:55.010 --> 01:56.897
Really great, actually.
Umm...

01:57.650 --> 01:58.997
She's a doctor now.

02:00.220 --> 02:03.580
And-and in a few weeks,
she's gonna get married to,

02:03.580 --> 02:05.861
<i>well,
an-an awesome guy.</i>

02:08.400 --> 02:09.561
Ellie's getting married?

02:10.509 --> 02:11.558
She is.

02:14.310 --> 02:18.462
That, uh, that's actually
mainly why we're here.

02:19.850 --> 02:20.721
Ellie was really hoping

02:20.807 --> 02:22.869
that you might be there
to walk her down the aisle.

02:24.340 --> 02:26.247
I don't think
she would want me there.

02:27.250 --> 02:29.250
I-I mean, of course,
of course she does.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.076
We both do.

02:30.850 --> 02:32.111
It's not a good idea.

02:32.660 --> 02:34.521
<i>But tell her
that I'm happy for her.</i>

02:35.440 --> 02:37.370
Are you, are you joking?
You have to do this.

02:37.370 --> 02:38.880
<i>She's your daughter.
Don't you want to be there?</i>

02:38.880 --> 02:40.290
Charles, I can't...

02:40.290 --> 02:42.540
I-I don't want to hear
what you can't do.

02:42.540 --> 02:44.352
I've seen
what you can't do.

02:53.800 --> 02:55.947
I'm sorry.
I, uh...

02:59.260 --> 03:00.280
That came out wrong.

03:00.280 --> 03:01.070
No, it didn't.

03:02.770 --> 03:03.789
You're mad.

03:04.530 --> 03:06.779
I left,
and-and you're mad.

03:09.400 --> 03:13.580
Look, Dad, I'm not even
here for me really, okay?

03:13.580 --> 03:14.454
Right now, I just...

03:14.516 --> 03:16.587
I want you to come
home for Ellie, please.

03:18.570 --> 03:22.434
I like you coming up here
and fighting for Ellie.

03:24.870 --> 03:26.156
Makes me happy you...

03:27.638 --> 03:29.411
at least
had each other.

03:36.250 --> 03:38.130
Let me get
a few things together.

03:44.990 --> 03:46.027
Are you okay?

03:48.250 --> 03:49.333
Yeah, I think so.

03:50.220 --> 03:52.303
I mean,
I'm glad we found him for Ellie.

03:53.420 --> 03:54.592
And for you?

03:58.390 --> 03:59.035
Yeah.

04:01.670 --> 04:04.224
Maybe he's not as crazy
as I remembered.

04:04.510 --> 04:05.105
<i>Okay.</i>

04:05.208 --> 04:06.942
Let's go get
your sister married, huh?

04:08.120 --> 04:10.782
Maybe we should wait till dark.
They're...

04:12.420 --> 04:14.155
They're tracking
my every move.

04:15.820 --> 04:16.906
<i>Rat bastards.</i>

04:20.154 --> 04:22.857
S02E19:
Chuck Versus The Dream Job

04:26.000 --> 04:32.769
Transcript:
YDY.com/BBS

